snippet.title: princess peachs's castle (gamecube tech demo!)- normal mode
snippet.description:
Hey! This is an video of an early GameCube tech-demo. It was released to show the power of the Gamecube to developers and was included in an early version of the Dolphin SDK. Its a neat demo and it shows off some cool effects like the bump and shadow, local lighting and Anti-Aliasing!

At 5:36 you can see an unreleased pink Gamecube.
This was running on the Wii  and all the music you hear is from the demo.

More info:
The tech demo has 2 modes, normal and auto. For this video I showcased the manual mode and this is where you can control the arrow. In auto mode the demo plays like a video, going threw the different rooms. You can also access the debug settings and change the how the GameCube renders the game and more! 

Thanks for watching;D

If you wondering what that blue and red bar does, it shows you the CPU and RAM the Cube/Wii is using.
